title: EditForge Pro
description: Inspiration: Growing up in Rwanda and working closely with students, cyber caf√©s, and self-taught developers, I noticed a common limitation: most creative and developer tools require constant internet access, subscriptions, or powerful devices. That left many talented people without access to basic tools they needed.  We asked ourselves ,what if creativity didn‚Äôt depend on any of that? What if someone could edit videos, compress images, test APIs, write code, convert files, or create documents, all in the browser, completely offline?  That‚Äôs what inspired EditForge Pro ‚Äî an all-in-one creative and developer suite designed to run entirely in the browser, with zero setup, zero sign-up, and complete privacy.  What it does EditForge Pro is a browser-based suite of over 25 tools that work completely offline. It covers a wide range of needs:  For creatives: video, audio, image editors, PDF tools, quote generators, and more  For developers: code editor, API tester, JSON formatter, hash and password tools  For students and researchers: text editor, lyrics finder, Wikipedia search  For everyday users: file converters, QR and calendar generators, screen recorder, unit converter, and more  All tools are designed to work without relying on APIs, external services, or user accounts. Everything runs locally, offering privacy and reliability.  How we built it EditForge Pro was developed using:  HTML, CSS (with Tailwind) for the user interface  Vanilla JavaScript modules for logic and tool isolation  Vite.js as the bundler and development environment  IndexedDB and LocalStorage to store preferences and process files locally  Service Workers for offline-first behavior  Netlify for free and fast global deployment  Each tool was built modularly, allowing them to work independently while sharing a consistent design and experience. title: Awaken
description: Awaken was born from one core frustration: self-help often feels boring, inconsistent, or overwhelming. Especially for young men who grew up on anime, games, and the internet. We wanted to build something better. A system that makes personal growth feel like leveling up your character, not checking off chores.  Most people already know what they should do. Go to the gym. Save money. Stay focused. But knowing isn‚Äôt the problem. The real struggle is staying consistent without structure, feedback, or a sense of momentum.  Awaken turns self-development into an RPG.  It gives each user daily AI-generated quests based on their goals across fitness, wealth, mindset, and relationships. Completing quests earns EXP, levels up their anime-style avatar, and drives real-world growth. Avatars are generated from selfies and evolve as the user does.  Core features include quest streaks, ranking systems, guilds, and optional social media locks for missed goals. Every detail is designed to feel like story-driven progress ‚Äî not just productivity.  Who it‚Äôs for: Ambitious young adults who want more from life but are tired of generic advice. Especially men aged 16 to 33 who grew up immersed in anime, gaming, and online culture. They don‚Äôt want a boring checklist. They want a system that speaks their language.  Awaken is not just another app. It is an identity builder, a discipline engine, and a culture in the making. We are reimagining what it means to grow.

title: AutoBoss: Build Your AI Agency in Minutes
description: Hey! So I'm Lakshya, just turned 18 and still figuring out this whole "adulting" thing while finishing high school. Got obsessed with AI after falling down way too many YouTube rabbit holes (probably should've been studying lol). The Problem That Drove Me Crazy: I really wanted to start something with AI - like, I had all these ideas but every single tool I looked at was either $200+ per month or required me to basically become a programmer overnight. I'm decent with computers but come on, I'm not trying to spend 6 months learning Python just to build a simple chatbot. It felt like being the only person without a driver's license trying to get somewhere. What I Built: AutoBoss is basically what I wished existed when I started - a no-code way for regular people to create AI stuff and actually make money from it. Think of it as training wheels for starting an AI agency, but the training wheels actually work really well. Who It's For: Anyone who's curious about AI but doesn't want to become a developer. I'm thinking freelancers who want to add AI services, small business owners, people in their 20s-40s who are tech-curious but not tech-experts. Basically people like my mom who can use Canva but would run away screaming from GitHub. What It Actually Does:  Client Workspaces - keeps your projects organized instead of having 47 browser tabs open AI Employee Builder - you can make chatbots or data analysis tools (added some badges because why not make it fun?) Document Training - upload PDFs or paste website URLs to teach your AI stuff Easy Sharing - send clients their AI tools through simple links  I built it mostly with Bolt.new (which is amazing btw), Firebase for the backend stuff, and Next.js. Did most of the coding between 11pm-2am because that's when my brain actually works. The Cool Part: In June, I got some people to test it and they were building working AI solutions in like 10-15 minutes. One person made a chatbot for a local bakery that actually helped them res

title: Wheely
description: Wheely was inspired by the growing need for flexible, short-term urban mobility across multiple vehicle types. In many cities, users are forced to rely on separate apps for bikes, scooters, or cars‚Äîor commit to expensive long-term rentals. Wheely solves this by offering an all-in-one platform where users can rent bicycles, scooters, motorbikes, and cars on an hourly basis. Designed for tourists, students, gig workers, and daily commuters, it allows users to browse nearby vehicles, select rental duration, and return them at designated drop zones. The app is built using React Native with Expo Router for seamless navigation, Lucide Icons for a clean UI, and Django Rest Framework on the backend. Key features include dynamic ride selection, intuitive modals, multi-language support, and a responsive UI for both Android and iOS. We also designed the system to be scalable‚Äîready for future integrations like GPS tracking, payments, referral programs, and even a unique Subletting feature where users can share unused rental time with others. With Wheely, we‚Äôre redefining short-term transportation as smarter, more flexible, and community-driven.

title: AI Resume Matcher
description: Last month, a friend of mine called me sounding defeated. He‚Äôd been applying to dozens of jobs, sending out resume after resume, and wasn‚Äôt getting a single callback. ‚ÄúI just wish I knew what I‚Äôm doing wrong,‚Äù he said. That one line hit me ‚Äî because I‚Äôve worked in the HR space for years, and I‚Äôve seen this happen from the other side too.  The truth is, most job applications never even make it to a recruiter. Around 78% of resumes get filtered out by software ‚Äî the ATS systems companies use to scan and shortlist candidates. Good people often get ignored simply because their resume doesn‚Äôt match the exact keywords or format the system is looking for. They‚Äôre not rejected for lack of talent ‚Äî they‚Äôre just lost in translation.  That‚Äôs when it clicked. With my experience in HR, I know how the backend works. I‚Äôve seen how systems scan resumes, what recruiters look for, and where candidates often go wrong. So I thought ‚Äî why not turn that insight into something useful for job seekers? Why not build a solution that gives people real feedback, based on how these systems actually work?  That‚Äôs how AI Resume Matcher was born. It‚Äôs a simple tool that helps job seekers stop guessing and start applying smarter. You just upload your resume, paste the job description (or job link), and get an instant match score. It shows you what you‚Äôre missing, what you‚Äôve done right, and exactly how to improve. If you need help fixing it, the AI can even generate improved resume content or a tailored cover letter on the spot.  This isn‚Äôt just another resume builder. It‚Äôs built from real HR experience, powered by smart AI, and designed to give job seekers the edge they need. Whether you're switching careers, just starting out, or trying to land that dream job ‚Äî this tool makes the process feel more in your control.  Instead of applying to 50 jobs and hearing nothing, people can now send 10 well-optimized resumes and actually get results. I‚Äôve seen how frustrating job searching can be ‚Äî and this i

title: TrafficIQ
description: What problem does it solve, or what inspired you to build it?  TrafficIQ solves the deadly crisis of unpredictable traffic congestion that costs lives, time, and trillions globally. I was inspired to build it after personally falling asleep in Lagos traffic and witnessing a patient die in an ambulance during the catastrophic Independence Bridge gridlock where people were trapped for 48+ hours - I realized we can predict weather and stock markets but people still drive blind into traffic disasters that kill and cost the global economy over $1 trillion annually.  Who is it for?  TrafficIQ is for daily commuters losing hours to traffic (like Lagos residents who lose 2 months yearly), emergency services needing life-saving priority routing, city governments requiring smart traffic management, logistics companies optimizing deliveries, and anyone who believes no one should die in traffic because we couldn't predict the predictable.  Key features, functionality, or integrations:  TrafficIQ provides 24-hour traffic predictions (world's first), emergency vehicle priority routing with dynamic corridors, AI-powered congestion hotspot identification, real-time alternative routes, and city-wide impact tracking that reduces commute times by 30-40%, built with Bolt.new for rapid development, Together AI for prediction algorithms, Supabase for real-time data, Google Maps API for traffic data, and deployed on Netlify - achieving 85% prediction accuracy and proving its worth by saving my 2-hour commute this morning!

title: Bryge AI - Your AI for ADHD communication
description: As a neurotypical person, I‚Äôve watched friends and coworkers with ADHD navigate a world that wasn‚Äôt built for their communication style, seeing the constant friction and immense mental effort it took to process a simple wall of text. The burden was always on them to adapt, and that didn‚Äôt sit right with me. I wanted to flip that script and build a bridge, which is why I created BRYGE AI. It‚Äôs an AI-powered communication assistant for any neurotypical person‚Äîa manager, a friend, or a partner‚Äîwho wants to connect more thoughtfully and effectively with the ADHD minds in their life. It goes far beyond grammar checkers to fundamentally reshape how a message is crafted and emotionally received. First, it acts as a personal coach, intelligently analyzing your original message for hidden pressure words and emotional triggers. Then, it transforms dense text into clean, emotionally safer language that you can customize with different tones and intents. Its standout feature, powered by ElevenLabs, is the ability to generate a personalized voice note in your own voice, which lowers the cognitive load for the recipient and eliminates the cold, robotic feel of other AI tools. Ultimately, BRYGE AI doesn‚Äôt just fix one message‚Äîit teaches you how to communicate better, helping you build the lasting habits of clarity, kindness, and emotional intelligence that reshape all your relationships.

title: Project Run
description: Project Run is a decentralized emergency response protocol designed for a world where centralized communication channels can fail. It was sparked by a single, chilling question: What happens when you can no longer trust the information you receive‚Äîor receive no information at all?  This functional prototype, built for the Bolt.new Hackathon, transforms any smartphone into a node in a peer-powered safety network. It's built for communities, enabling them to send, receive, and verify critical alerts without relying on central servers.  Key Features: - A full-stack application with a live Supabase backend for real-time alerts. - A multi-page dashboard for threat monitoring and reporting. - A community-based verification system to combat misinformation. - A "Trusted Circle" interface for personal network management.  The entire project, from concept and UI design to the full-stack integration, was built in under 72 hours through an intensive human-AI collaboration using Bolt.new, Gemini, and other AI tools.

title: LifeBeacon Rescue/Civil
description: LifeBeacon revolutionizes emergency rescue by transforming smartphones into life-saving beacons for trapped victims during disasters. The Problem: In 2024, 10,000+ people died under rubble after earthquakes and building collapses. Current rescue methods using dogs, thermal cameras, or manual searching are often too slow during the critical first 48 hours when every minute counts. The Solution: A dual-app emergency system creating direct communication between trapped victims and rescue teams. Nearly everyone carries a powerful beacon - their smartphone. LifeBeacon unlocks this potential to dramatically reduce search time. LifeBeacon Civil (for civilians - https://serene-kelpie-605da4.netlify.app/):  Automatic emergency signals when app installed Large stress-resistant SOS button for conscious victims Receives wake commands from rescue teams Optimized battery management for extended operation under debris Discreet mode for dangerous situations  LifeBeacon Rescue (complementary app for emergency responders):  Real-time radar detection of civilian signals Advanced filtering by priority, battery level, and distance Remote wake commands to trigger sounds/vibrations on victim phones Team coordination and mission management  Key Innovation: Creates a direct communication bridge between trapped victims and rescue teams, potentially saving thousands of lives through technology everyone already carries. Built with Bolt.new by a first-time developer in 3 days, proving that determination and AI-powered development can create life-saving solutions.

We wanted a solution that lets students upload their study material and stay locked in ‚Äî learning, asking AI questions, and watching only the right videos ‚Äî all in one focused space. That‚Äôs how SuperArc was born:  An AI-powered, distraction-free study platform that helps students focus deeply and build their comeback arc.  What it does SuperArc is a productivity-first platform designed for students and self-learners. It lets users:  Upload PDFs, notes, or any study materials Use AI to ask questions contextually based on their material Get YouTube video suggestions relevant to the topic they're reading Summarize long content instantly Auto-generate flashcards after each topic Study in Pomodoro mode with streak tracking and gamified progress Unlock badges like "Ignition" and "Locked In" based on study discipline All of this happens within a dark-mode, focused workspace ‚Äî built to help users stay in the zone. Our solution is an SMS-based scavenger hunt that guides users through urban street art discoveries. The platform uses Twilio for text messaging interactions and Supabase for secure authentication. Users explore cities through graffiti pieces and locations stored in our database, unlocking new experiences at their own pace. We're building organic reach through automatically generated blog content based on our cataloged street art and partnerships. Our partnership pages are already ranking well in Google searches, creating a sustainable growth channel. The platform is fully monetized with Stripe integration for seamless payments. The concept was inspired by a personal experience exploring historic buildings in London, but evolved to focus specifically on street art to create a more vibrant, contemporary urban adventure.

Polylogue solves this by delivering contextualized, level-appropriate stories and animations, supported by images, gestures, and native audio ‚Äî just like how we naturally acquire language. title: LaunchPad
description: Recruitment in Bangladesh is so flawed that the students of my country had to overthrow the government in an attempt to reform it.  Entry-level jobs ask for 2-3 years of ‚Äúwork experience‚Äù, have sky-high credential requirements (which are often unrelated to the job) and the interview process often lasts for months on end. Moreover, recruiters often favor those from more prestigious Universities or those with referrals.  Employers are always complaining about ‚Äúnot finding talent with the right practical skills‚Äù but skilled job seekers in Bangladesh are often overlooked due to the above reasons.  LaunchPad connects employers to skilled talent and skilled talent to opportunities that they have long been deprived of.  Here‚Äôs how:  Employers post the job description and a short task that is related to the job, such as making a to-do app for an app development job. Instead of just putting in a resume, the candidate has to finish the task and upload it along with their skill portfolio.  This way, employers can directly evaluate the candidate‚Äôs practical skills without any bias. Additionally, this ensures only those with the relevant skills can apply, which means candidates don‚Äôt get their application buried by thousands of irrelevant people spamming their resumes on every job. Another problem is that many graduates don‚Äôt even know what practical skills they would need for their dream job. To solve this, we used ChatGPT-3.5-turbo API integration to analyse the user‚Äôs skill level and job target to build a custom roadmap with skill-building challenges to help them build up their skills & portfolio. We‚Äôre not just a job posting site, we‚Äôre the leaders of a movement to make hiring fair for all.

title: HealthCostBenefit
description: This project, "HealthCostBenefit - Evidence-Based Supplement Analysis," is designed to help individuals make informed decisions about dietary supplements by providing a data-driven approach to evaluating their cost-effectiveness.  The core problem it solves is the lack of clear, evidence-based information regarding the true value and return on investment (ROI) of various supplements. Many consumers purchase supplements without understanding their potential health benefits in quantifiable terms or their economic impact. This platform aims to bridge that gap by applying principles of health economics, specifically Quality-Adjusted Life Years (QALYs), to supplement analysis.  It is primarily for health-conscious individuals, researchers, and anyone looking to understand the scientific and economic rationale behind supplement use.  Key features and functionality include:  AI-Powered Database Expansion: The application leverages AI to automatically research, validate, and populate a comprehensive database of supplements. This involves integrating with external APIs like PubMed for scientific literature, RapidAPI for real-time pricing data, and OpenAI for synthesizing complex information into understandable supplement profiles. It also includes robust validation and cleanup mechanisms to ensure data quality. Quantifiable Health Benefits: It translates the health outcomes associated with supplements into QALY gains, providing a standardized measure of health improvement. Cost-Benefit Analysis: Users can see the calculated ROI for supplements, comparing their monthly cost against their estimated health benefit value. Interactive Visualizations: The platform presents complex data through intuitive charts and comparison tables, allowing users to easily compare different supplements side-by-side. Reporting and Export: Users can generate and export detailed PDF reports or print-friendly versions of their analyses. Supabase Integration: All supplement data is persistently stored

description: NutureAI is an AI-powered, culturally-intelligent health companion. It aims to provide health guidance that understands and respects an individual's cultural background, food traditions, and lifestyle preferences. Many existing health applications recommend approaches that don't align with the cultural practices or traditional healing foods of various communities. This leads to a disconnect where health technology fails to serve the full spectrum of how people live, eat, and find joy in movement.  NutureAI's solution is to offer personalized coaching that learns an individual's life, not just their data, by considering their schedule, preferences, family dynamics, and cultural context. It also fosters community connection, creating a "cultural health village" where users can connect with others who share their background and health journey. The core mission is to ensure that every person receives health guidance that celebrates their culture, rather than erasing it. NutureAI offers three key benefits:  Cultural Adaptation: It honors your food heritage by using AI that understands traditional foods, cooking methods, and cultural health practices from your background. I‚Äôd often find myself wondering:  Didn‚Äôt I already write a better version of this somewhere?  Which version did I use for that last successful interview? title: KBD Guardian ‚Äî The AI That Stops Dialysis Before It Starts A beautiful, real-time health assistant for managing Kidney, Blood Pressure & Diabetes with AI-powered tracking, reminders, lab uploads, doctor sync, & life-saving analytics ‚Äî all in 1 dashboard.
description: It started with silence. The silence of a father who missed one insulin dose too many. The silence of a grandmother who couldn't recall when her BP shot up. And the crushing silence in dialysis wards ‚Äî where every patient started with just a few missed signs.  Every 3 out of 5 kidney failures begin with uncontrolled diabetes or blood pressure. Each dialysis patient costs families and health systems up to $60,000/year. But the biggest cost? Time lost, dignity compromised, and decisions delayed.  So we sat with patients. We interviewed doctors. We sifted through handwritten charts, broken apps, and forgotten prescriptions.  They all echoed the same pain:  ‚ÄúI don‚Äôt remember what changed last time.‚Äù  ‚ÄúWhich app was I using again?‚Äù  ‚ÄúI missed my follow-up.‚Äù  ‚ÄúI forgot when to take my meds.‚Äù  That‚Äôs when we knew ‚Äî data wasn‚Äôt enough. They didn‚Äôt need another tracker. They needed a memory. A guide. A medical companion.  And so, we built KBD Guardian ‚Äî the AI-powered health guardian that thinks like a doctor and cares like family.  What it does KBD Guardian is a mobile-first, real-time medical web app that tracks and connects all vital signs for kidney patients, diabetics, and those with high blood pressure ‚Äî while keeping doctors and caregivers always in the loop.

title: SpeakDude is an language learning platform that focuses on real conversation practice through realistic AI avatars and translation challenges
description: The idea for SpeakDude came from a deeply personal struggle that millions of language learners face every day. Like many others, I wanted to become fluent in English, but I found myself constantly stumbling over words, hesitating mid-sentence, and making embarrassing mistakes. The fear of being judged by others was so overwhelming that I often chose silence over speaking, which only made my fluency worse.  I realized that traditional language learning apps focus heavily on grammar rules and vocabulary memorization, but they completely miss the most crucial skill: actually speaking. You can know thousands of words and perfect grammar, but if you can't speak confidently in real conversations, you're not truly fluent.  The breakthrough moment came when I understood that what language learners really need is a judgment-free practice partner - someone who won't laugh at mistakes, won't get impatient with stuttering, and is available 24/7 to practice with.  Features  AI Avatar Conversations with Luna:  Practice with Luna, a lifelike AI language tutor powered by Tavus  Supports 30 languages Real-time video conversations with natural speech recognition and responses Judgement Free environment to practice   Rapid Translation:  AI-generated sentences with configurable difficulty levels (Beginner, Intermediate, Advanced) Speech-to-text recognition for your responses using OpenAI Whisper Real-time AI evaluation and scoring system Timed challenges to build quick thinking skills in your target language Instant feedback to help correct mistakes  Comprehensive Progress Tracking  Visual activity calendar showing daily learning streaks Detailed analytics: total sessions, time spent, average scores, current streak Session history with performance trends  Built using  BOLT.new ‚Äì Build full applications just by chatting with AI. title: YouLookedAt.me
description: A missed connection is when two people briefly cross paths, feel a possible connection, but don‚Äôt get the chance to talk further or exchange contact information.  I once had a brief interaction with a girl. We smiled at each other. I saw her again on a beach, but I wasn‚Äôt confident enough to approach her. I didn‚Äôt know her name, who her friends were, or where she studied. It was a huge city, and I knew the chances of ever seeing her again were slim unless destiny had something planned. But I wasn‚Äôt that lucky. I never saw her again.  Even now, that moment stays with me. I often wonder how two strangers who felt something could they ever find each other again. If they don‚Äôt know names, addresses, or any personal details. That question stayed with me and eventually sparked the idea for this project.  YouLookedAt.me is a platform where you can share your missed connection moment. If someone else posts a story that matches yours, you‚Äôll be notified and can start a chat. It‚Äôs a space to share real, heartfelt stories, post anonymous notes, and maybe even reconnect with someone you briefly crossed paths with.  It‚Äôs all about second chances and real stories because sometimes destiny just needs a little help.

title: The Mind Share
description: ## Inspiration The Mind Share was born from a deeply personal struggle. For years, despite a history of academic success, I found myself battling severe memory and concentration problems. These cognitive gaps began to profoundly affect my life, my work, and my ability to learn new things. The breaking point came during my professional career; I failed multiple job interviews due to an inability to recall key details under pressure, and in the rare instances I was hired, my tenure lasted only a few days.  Facing this reality, I decided I had to act. I couldn't find a job that could accommodate my challenges, so I resolved to create my own. My goal was to build the very tool I needed‚Äîa solution not just for me, but for anyone else feeling adrift in a sea of mental fog. title: Flights Overhead
description: About This Project: Flights Overhead  What Inspired Me  I flew from San Diego to Seattle, then Seattle to Victoria, BC yesterday for a vacation! As I approached each airport, I found myself watching planes take off and land, and wondered: Where are they going? Where did they come from?  That same curiosity often strikes me at home - I live below a flight path and constantly hear aircraft flying overhead. I wanted a tool that could tell me, in real-time, where those planes are headed or returning from. This app is the result of that moment of curiosity.  What I Learned  This was my first time working with both the Mapbox Geocoding API and the FlightAware AeroAPI, and I‚Äôm thrilled with how much I‚Äôve expanded my understanding of live geospatial APIs.  I also gained hands-on experience with Supabase Edge Functions, which helped me improve my error handling, environment variable management, and middleware API routing.  How I Built It  The entire application was structured from one comprehensive Bolt prompt that included:  Geolocation and address-based input Mapbox Geocoding to turn addresses into coordinates FlightAware to fetch live nearby flights and calculate the closest one Supabase Edge Function to handle secure API calls React + Tailwind + open-source fonts for a responsive, vintage-style frontend Mobile-first layout with full accessibility, loading states, and error handling Every piece of functionality and design was planned in that initial Bolt prompt. Follow-up prompts were used only for fixing Supabase edge function errors and polishing output. Built With  Bolt (one-prompt workflow) Supabase Mapbox Geocoding API FlightAware AeroAPI React, Tailwind CSS, and TypeScript Fonts: Share Tech Mono, DM Sans

Without any tuition or extra prep, I consistently top my Spanish class, just by casually doing Duolingo every day.  That‚Äôs what inspired my dad and me:  "Why isn‚Äôt the rest of school this effortless and fun?"  We started brainstorming. What followed by days of research and reading on what makes Duolingo click. Chunking, Micro Learning, and Spaced repetitions. What if we took the same bite-sized, gamified learning model and applied it to school subjects, especially ones I and my classmates struggle with? That‚Äôs how Vidyaa was born.  It started as a way for me to dogfood my own learning, and has grown into a much larger vision.  üß† What We Learned Gamified micro-learning works incredibly well, especially for people with short attention spans. (I am the proof.) Students don‚Äôt hate studying; they hate boring, one-size-fits-all methods. AI + education = powerful combo. It can personalize, adapt, and accelerate mastery. Building something for yourself first is the best way to make sure it works. üõ†Ô∏è How We Built It We started with subjects I study in school, like English, Maths, Physics, etc for IGCSE Class 9 & 10. We broke down chapters into bite-sized lessons, and used AI to generate:  Subjects, Sections and Units with bite-sized courses for learning Smart, spaced quizzes Active recall challenges Personalized learning journeys We used:  React Native for a sleek mobile-first UI Supabase and Node.js backend Perplexity & ChatGPT to generate curriculum-aligned content and auto-grade quiz responses A tutor marketplace for students needing 1:1 help from subject experts Everything was tested and refined using my real class curriculum. title: One Moment a Day
description: One Moment A Day A beautifully designed mobile journaling app that helps users capture and reflect on meaningful moments from their daily lives.  Inspiration The inspiration for "One Moment A Day" came from the desire to create a mindful, intentional journaling experience that encourages users to pause and reflect on the meaningful moments in their daily lives. In our fast-paced world, we often miss the small joys and insights that make life beautiful. This app was born from the belief that taking just one moment each day to reflect can lead to greater self-awareness, gratitude, and personal growth.  The concept emphasizes quality over quantity - rather than overwhelming users with lengthy journaling requirements, it focuses on capturing that one special moment, thought, or feeling that stood out each day. This approach makes journaling accessible and sustainable for people who might feel intimidated by traditional journaling apps.  What it does "One Moment A Day" is a beautifully designed mobile journaling app that helps users capture and reflect on meaningful moments from their daily lives. Here's what makes it special:  Core Features: Daily Prompts: Each day presents users with a thoughtful, randomly selected prompt to inspire reflection (e.g., "What made you smile today?", "Describe a moment that surprised you today") One Entry Per Day: Users can only save one entry per day, encouraging intentional reflection rather than overwhelming journaling. Beautiful UI: Features an aurora-inspired background with smooth animations and a calming color scheme Offline-First: Works seamlessly offline with automatic sync when connection is restored End-to-End Encryption: All journal entries are encrypted using user-specific keys for complete privacy Smart Notifications: Personalized reminder notifications that adapt based on user's streak and behavior Streak Tracking: Motivates users with current and longest streak tracking Search & History: Easy access to past entries with sea

title: Adifi
description: Inspiration As a 15-year-old JEE aspirant, my life is built around study schedules, problem sets, and pressure. Everyone around me expects academic excellence, not creative expression. I‚Äôve often heard:  ‚ÄúCoding won‚Äôt take you anywhere right now.‚Äù ‚ÄúWhy waste time on side projects?‚Äù  But I‚Äôve always known that I wasn‚Äôt built just to follow a syllabus. I wanted to build something that felt like mine.  Late one night, drained after coaching, I opened Bolt.New. No installs, no distractions ‚Äî just an open canvas and a crazy idea:  What if photo editing could be lightning-fast, powerful like Photoshop, simple like Canva, and all in the browser?  That‚Äôs how ADIFI was born. Not just a tool, but my rebellion against rote learning and my belief that I can create something real ‚Äî even when no one believes in me.  What it does Adifi(AKA photo studio pro) is a lightning-fast, privacy-first photo editor that works completely in-browser. It combines the precision of Photoshop with the simplicity of Canva, without requiring any downloads or uploads.  Features:  Multi-layer editing (images, text, effects)  Real-time filters (brightness, contrast, blur, vignette, etc.)  AI-powered background removal (using BodyPix)  Instant exports (with zero server processing)  Fully responsive UI with keyboard shortcuts and live previews  How we built it Built entirely in Bolt.New using vibe coding ‚Äî described my vision and let AI scaffold the architecture.  Used React + TypeScript with Tailwind CSS for structure and styling.  Built a custom Canvas engine to handle layers, effects, and pixel manipulations.  Integrated TensorFlow.js and BodyPix for client-side AI features like background removal.  Added undo/redo functionality, image state tracking, and real-time performance stats.  Challenges we ran into Balancing studies and coding: Working on ADIFI late at night, after long coaching days, was emotionally and mentally draining.  Performance bottlenecks: Large image processing would slow the browse

title: Impact Taps
description: I wanted to explore whether a simple interactive experience could leave a lasting emotional impact. We‚Äôre constantly surrounded by statistics about war, climate change, and social issues, but they often feel distant or abstract. I wondered‚Äîwhat if we could sneak that awareness in through something unexpected?  Impact Taps looks like a game at first. You tap for 10 seconds, thinking it's about speed or reflexes. But when the timer ends, you‚Äôre shown your score as a real-world statistic‚Äîlike the number of children killed in conflict zones last year, or the amount of plastic dumped into the ocean every day. The surprise makes people stop and think. That‚Äôs the goal.  This was built entirely using one prompt on Bolt.new. The app uses JavaScript to track taps, a 10-second timer, and a simple local JSON file filled with verified statistics. No backend, no fancy logic. Just a clean interface and one strong emotional reveal.  Impact Taps is for anyone who scrolls the web mindlessly and needs a moment of perspective. It‚Äôs quick, frictionless, and designed to catch people off guard‚Äîin a good way.

title: Video Prompt Crafter
description: Creating high quality AI generated videos is both time consuming and expensive. Crafting the perfect prompt often requires multiple iterations, and generic prompts typically focus only on basic elements like the subject and environment while ignoring critical cinematic aspects such as camera angles, shot types, lighting, and visual effects.  As video generation becomes more mainstream, creators need a smarter way to build rich and detailed prompts that translate into visually compelling results.   I took a cinematic scene and reverse-engineered it, breaking it down into key components:  Character & Action ‚Äì including Age, Subject, Emotion, and Activity. Environment & Atmosphere ‚Äì such as Location, Time of Day, and Mood. Cinematic Details ‚Äì like Camera Shot Type, Movement, and Angle. Visuals & Tone ‚Äì covering Lighting, Aesthetics, VFX, Color Palette, Audio, and Resolution. Dialogue ‚Äì for adding spoken elements.  By filling in these guided inputs, you‚Äôre essentially crafting a complete cinematic scene‚Äîone that‚Äôs ready to be copied directly into AI video generation platforms for high-quality output.

title: Pohi AI Pro
description: ### **Inspiration**  The inspiration for Pohi AI Pro came directly from real-world experience in the acacia wood pole manufacturing industry. Selling these products globally highlighted significant inefficiencies and a clear need for a centralized system to connect manufacturers with ready stock to customers looking to place orders, and to streamline the complex logistics involved.  ### **What it does**  Pohi AI Pro is a sophisticated database and logistics application designed to revolutionize how manufacturers and their customers interact. At its core, it:  * **Connects Stakeholders:** It serves as a central hub for customers (buyers) to submit their product demands and for manufacturers to list their available stock.   * **Manages Orders & Stock:** The system facilitates the uploading of detailed order requirements by customers and available inventory by manufacturers. A key feature is its AI-powered capability to automatically match these demands with suitable stock.   * **Provides Role-Specific Interfaces:** It offers tailored user interfaces for three distinct roles:     * **Customers:** Can submit new demands (including specialized ones like acacia pole orders) and track their existing demands, benefiting from AI suggestions for alternatives or status explanations.     * **Manufacturers:** Can list new stock items, manage their inventory, and leverage AI tools for price suggestions, marketing text generation, product photo generation, and listing quality analysis.     * **Administrators:** Have a comprehensive overview of the platform, manage users and system-wide stock, utilize advanced AI-driven matchmaking tools, plan logistics (including truck loading and routing), handle billing, and access AI-generated reports and system health dashboards.

title: Amara
description: Amara is your personal AI Mental Wellness Assistant, designed to make empathetic emotional support and self-exploration accessible to everyone, anytime, anywhere. It's for anyone seeking a compassionate listener and a guide on their journey to inner calm, offering support without the typical constraints of cost or availability.  Key Features & Functionality:  Empathetic AI Conversations: Users can engage in natural, flowing conversations through both text and seamless voice interactions, powered by a sophisticated LLM and ElevenLabs for realistic voice synthesis. title: CycleWise
description: A woman‚Äôs monthly cycle has phases that affect her mood, energy, and stress levels. CycleWise gives husbands gentle alerts and simple guidance on when and how to show the support that truly matters. I have observed how the understanding, or misunderstanding, of emotions between spouses can make or break the peace in a home. In many cases, I saw how domestic tension, even violence against women, often stemmed from emotional misinterpretation.  This got me asking the question: "What if men knew more about the emotions of their wives?" I began researching how much men knew about the emotional cycles of women. I interviewed some married men and asked the question "Are you aware that your wife‚Äôs monthly cycle influences her emotions and behavior?" Over 98% had no idea. They were often shocked and remorseful. A common reaction was: ‚ÄúIf I had known this earlier, I would have been more patient and supportive.‚Äù  This became my initial inspiration to build an app that gives husbands the insight to understand and support the emotional health of their wives. The next inspiration was their willingness to pay a token for monthly subscription (one responder promised to donate to the product), and the final inspiration is that the tools to easily build it was made available by Bolt's hackathon. What it does  CycleWise gives husbands the insight to understand and support the emotional health of their wives. It uses the cycle start date to calculate the emotionally sensitive phase, and sends monthly alert and support tips, a day before it starts. I believe it can improve marriage relationships and help to build more peaceful homes. How we built it  I interviewed 8 married men in an effort to validate the idea, and got them on the wait-list. Bolt.New was used to build all core functionalities till it was production-ready with: Payment processing (Paystack for Nigeria, Stripe for international) Supabase integration with payment status tracking Beautiful, responsive design Email collect

title: PurpleVerse
description: üí°What problem does it solve, or what inspired you to build it? Who is it for?  PurpleVerse was inspired by the frustrating limitations people in low-income countries face when shopping online ‚Äî especially when it comes to international payments, FOREX instability, and platform restrictions. Traditional e-commerce is often inaccessible or expensive for users in these regions, and that creates a digital divide in global trade.  I wanted to solve this by creating a borderless e-commerce platform that leverages crypto (USDC on Algorand Testnet for the prototype) as the means of payment. This removes the need for traditional financial systems and enables secure, trustless transactions worldwide ‚Äî even for physical goods.  PurpleVerse is for:  Buyers who want to shop globally without payment restrictions.  Sellers looking to reach wider markets and access intelligent tools.  Emerging markets underserved by mainstream payment systems.   üîë Key Features & Functionality  Crypto-Powered Payments Secure, escrow-based crypto transactions using USDC on Algorand. Funds are held until buyers confirm delivery.  Mock Wallet Integration For demo purposes, a hardcoded mock wallet simulates crypto payments and release flows.  AI-Assisted Seller Tools Sellers get help writing product descriptions, tracking analytics, and managing inventory through AI-powered features.  Admin Dashboard Full control panel to manage users, roles, featured products, commissions, and blog content.  Flash Sales & Featured Listings Sellers can run time-limited offers or pay to boost product visibility across the platform.  Platform Revenue Model 5% commission on every sale + featured product placement fees, all automated.  Blog and AI Chatbot (Support) Includes a built-in blog CMS and AI chatbot to assist buyers and sellers with FAQs and navigation.   üîå Built With:  Frontend: React + TypeScript + Tailwind + Vite  Backend: Supabase (auth, DB, storage, functions, RLS)  Blockchain: Algorand (Testnet) using algo

title: Tagramp üöÄ
description: As a founder I attend countless pitch nights, demo days, and coffee meet-ups. By the end of each week my pockets are stuffed with business cards and my LinkedIn inbox is full of ‚Äúnice to meet you‚Äù messages, but when a real problem surfaces I cannot remember which of those contacts actually fits the challenge. I wanted a tool that would treat every introduction as data, tie it to my business goals, and surface the one expert or company that can move the needle right now. Tagramp began as that personal itch: turning random networking into a goal-centric, ROI-driven engine for growth and collaboration. What it does Tagramp is an AI-first SaaS platform that converts static contact lists into living, goal-oriented opportunities.  AI profile generation I paste a website URL, PDF deck, or plain text. Natural-language models summarise the material and create a concise company or personal profile plus a short list of top-level goals.  Goal-centric matching Those goals feed an intelligent matcher that scans verified professionals and organisations‚Äîeither public communities or networks I import. The algorithm scores each potential connection on relevance, complementary expertise, and past success.  Instant collaboration framework When a match is found the system produces a ‚ÄúRamp-a-Plan,‚Äù an editable roadmap and a ready-to-send introduction email. Instead of starting from ‚Äúlet‚Äôs grab coffee,‚Äù both sides see clear next steps and mutual value from day one.  Monetisable networks As a community owner I can charge subscription fees so only vetted members appear in match results, which preserves quality and creates a revenue stream.  Built-in relationship tracking A light CRM layer records email threads, Slack or WhatsApp chats, calendar events, and call notes so progress is measurable from first hello to closed deal. I was honestly amazed at how intuitive and smart Bolt was ‚Äì sometimes it even understood my needs better than I could explain them!  I learned a lot during the process: new development terms, UI/UX logic, how to build live dashboards, manage user roles, create smart alerts, and set up powerful automations and external integrations. I published the app using Netlify, and although I tried to connect a personal domain via ENTRI, I ran into technical issues ‚Äì which became a valuable part of the learning journey.  Now, I'm proud not only of the app, but of the entire process ‚Äì turning a real need into a smart, automated solution that supports staff, protects students, and opens the door to even more innovation ahead.

description: üí°What problem does it solve, or what inspired you to build it? Who is it for?  PurpleVerse was inspired by the frustrating limitations people in low-income countries face when shopping online ‚Äî especially when it comes to international payments, FOREX instability, and platform restrictions. Traditional e-commerce is often inaccessible or expensive for users in these regions, and that creates a digital divide in global trade.  I wanted to solve this by creating a borderless e-commerce platform that leverages crypto (USDC on Algorand Testnet for the prototype) as the means of payment. This removes the need for traditional financial systems and enables secure, trustless transactions worldwide ‚Äî even for physical goods.  PurpleVerse is for:  Buyers who want to shop globally without payment restrictions.  Sellers looking to reach wider markets and access intelligent tools.  Emerging markets underserved by mainstream payment systems.   üîë Key Features & Functionality  Crypto-Powered Payments Secure, escrow-based crypto transactions using USDC on Algorand. Funds are held until buyers confirm delivery.  Mock Wallet Integration For demo purposes, a hardcoded mock wallet simulates crypto payments and release flows.  AI-Assisted Seller Tools Sellers get help writing product descriptions, tracking analytics, and managing inventory through AI-powered features.  Admin Dashboard Full control panel to manage users, roles, featured products, commissions, and blog content.  Flash Sales & Featured Listings Sellers can run time-limited offers or pay to boost product visibility across the platform.  Platform Revenue Model 5% commission on every sale + featured product placement fees, all automated.  Blog and AI Chatbot (Support) Includes a built-in blog CMS and AI chatbot to assist buyers and sellers with FAQs and navigation.   üîå Built With:  Frontend: React + TypeScript + Tailwind + Vite  Backend: Supabase (auth, DB, storage, functions, RLS)  Blockchain: Algorand (Testnet) using algo

title: renat.ai
description: The renat.ai project was inspired by the vision of creating an advanced artificial general intelligence (AGI) assistant that can effectively help users with a wide range of tasks. The core problem it aims to solve is providing an intelligent, secure, and user-friendly conversational AI experience, moving beyond basic chatbots to offer deeper knowledge and assistance. It's built to showcase the potential of integrating powerful AI models with robust, modern web technologies.  This project is primarily for users seeking an intelligent conversational partner for various inquiries, from technology and science to general assistance. It's also a valuable resource for developers and AI enthusiasts interested in how a full-stack AI application can be built with a focus on security, performance, and user experience.  Here are some of its key features, functionalities, and integrations:  Advanced AI Integration: At its heart, renat.ai integrates with the OpenAI API to provide sophisticated chat capabilities, allowing it to understand and respond to complex queries. Secure Authentication and Database: It uses Supabase for robust user authentication and as its PostgreSQL database, ensuring secure user management and persistent storage of chat messages. Comprehensive Security Measures: Security is a paramount concern, with features like: Content Security Policy (CSP) configured in netlify.toml to prevent cross-site scripting (XSS) attacks. Input Validation and Rate Limiting (src/lib/security.ts) to protect against abuse and ensure data integrity. Secure Headers (HSTS, X-Frame-Options, X-Content-Type-Options, X-XSS-Protection) for enhanced browser security. Secure Logging (src/lib/logger.ts) for monitoring security events and authentication attempts. Modern Frontend Development: The application is built with React and TypeScript, styled with Tailwind CSS for a responsive and visually appealing interface, and uses Lucide React for a consistent icon set. Dynamic User Experience: It

title: Flights Overhead
description: What Inspired Me I flew from San Diego to Seattle, then Seattle to Victoria, BC yesterday for a vacation! As I approached each airport, I found myself watching planes take off and land, and wondered: Where are they going? Where did they come from?  That same curiosity often strikes me at home - I live below a flight path and constantly hear aircraft flying overhead. I wanted a tool that could tell me, in real-time, where those planes are headed or returning from. This app is the result of that moment of curiosity.  What I Learned This was my first time working with both the Mapbox Geocoding API and the FlightAware AeroAPI, and I‚Äôm thrilled with how much I‚Äôve expanded my understanding of live geospatial APIs.  I also gained hands-on experience with Supabase Edge Functions, which helped me improve my error handling, environment variable management, and middleware API routing.  How I Built It The entire application was structured from one comprehensive Bolt prompt that included:  Geolocation and address-based input Mapbox Geocoding to turn addresses into coordinates FlightAware to fetch live nearby flights and calculate the closest one Supabase Edge Function to handle secure API calls React + Tailwind + open-source fonts for a responsive, vintage-style frontend Mobile-first layout with full accessibility, loading states, and error handling Every piece of functionality and design was planned in that initial Bolt prompt. Follow-up prompts were used only for fixing Supabase edge function errors and polishing output.

title: Platform for field hockey coaches
description: doHockey is the smart assistant for field hockey coaches. From drag-and-drop lineups to automatic substitution schedules and real-time playtime tracking, it simplifies match-day management. Stay focused on the game‚ÄîdoHockey handles the logistics.  ##Why doHockey? As an amateur field hockey coach, I know how much time and effort goes into managing a team ‚Äî especially on busy weekends. Planning lineups, tracking playtime, and organizing substitutions often takes more time than the match itself. That‚Äôs why I developed doHockey: a practical, time-saving tool designed to take the hassle out of match-day management.  doHockey helps coaches stay focused on the game by handling the logistics. You can easily create lineups with a drag-and-drop interface, automatically generate substitution schedules based on preset intervals, and track each player‚Äôs playtime in real time. Whether you want to rotate players every 6 or 9 minutes, or ensure fair playing time for everyone, doHockey makes it simple.  The tool supports standard match settings ‚Äî four quarters of 17.5 minutes, with up to five reserves ‚Äî and provides a live dashboard during the match, along with a printable substitution schedule to keep things running smoothly on the sidelines.  doHockey is built for coaches like me, who love the sport but could use a bit of help staying organized. It saves time, reduces stress, and ensures every player gets the attention they deserve.  Inspiration  As an amateur field hockey coach, I often spend more time planning than coaching. Organizing lineups, substitutions, and tracking playtime ‚Äî especially during weekend matches ‚Äî can be stressful and inefficient. I wanted a tool to take care of the logistics so I could focus on the team and the game.

Community Experience: Patients can share their health journeys, support each other, and learn from collective experiences‚Äîvital in countries where hospitals are scarce.  Doctor & Patient Dashboards: Secure record-keeping, real-time messaging, appointment management, and more.  Pandemic-ready: Enables remote triage, care, and support during health crises.  Integrations: Built on Supabase for secure storage & authentication, OpenAI for smart AI chat, and ElevenLabs for natural voice interactions.

description: Inspiration When I started prepping for the TEF Canada exam, most resources felt lifeless and disconnected and didn‚Äôt reflect the actual test. I kept thinking, Why isn‚Äôt there something that just feels like the real exam? After extensive research I found out that there is no such product out there. So we built it. Reading & Listening: Realistic practice in the style and timing of the official exam Writing & Speaking: Instantly evaluated by AI, mapped to CLB levels Progress Dashboard: See what‚Äôs working, fix what‚Äôs not, and stay motivated with visual milestones How We Built It Bolt-Powered Sprint: We used bolt.new to move fast frontend, backend, and AI evaluation all spun up in one platform Exam Reverse Engineering: We mapped out the TEF structure by breaking down every section type and scoring rubric AI Scoring: LLM handles writing and speaking tasks by evaluating clarity and structure.
